{
  "texts": [
    "Specifically, while the channel attention network possesses dynamic global receptive fields, it lacks the desired inductive bias.",
    "On the other hand, convolution neural network exhibit strong inductive biases but are limited by their deficiency in large receptive fields.",
    "Thus, it remains unclear whether fusing these two networks can yield improved performance in scene classification.",
    "In order to address this issue, we have proposed a new architecture called RCA by combining the strengths of both residual and channel attention, as shown in Fig. 2.The proposed Residual Channel-attention network (RCA) introduces a novel approach to scene classification in high-resolution remote sensing images, addressing the specific limitations of traditional convolutional neural networks (CNNs).",
    "Traditional CNNs are effective at extracting spatial features but often struggle to capture complex semantic relationships between objects at varying scales."
  ]
}